HEADWORD: Lithophyte
<hw>Lith"o*phyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Litho-</ets> + Gr. <?/ plant: cf. F.
<ets>lithophyte</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A hard, or stony,
plantlike organism, as the gorgonians, corals, and corallines, esp.
those gorgonians having a calcareous axis. All the lithophytes except
the corallines are animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lithophytic</ent>⟦br⟧
